The paper deals with the analysis of vessel morphology and connectivity, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of tensor fields and fast marching algorithms suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and machine learning (cs.MM), while the validation of the method on synthetic and real images indicates a practical application of the proposed approach. The evaluation of performance metrics such as accuracy, precision and recall suggests a focus on neural networks and optimization (cs.NE), while the comparison with classical and state-of-the-art methods suggests a focus on machine learning and computer graphics (cs.LG).
